column1: #Text=( running computer hardware at a higher clock rate than normally ) is more of an enjoyment for senior gamers or engineers , while the average computer users may lack the basic concepts of it , causing hardware to halt when they attempt it .

#Text=With those issues in mind , Wikinews freelance reporter Rico Shen interviewed Peter " Shamino " Tan , an overclocking expert from Singapore , to clear up some of the basic issues relating to overclocking .
#Text=It was nice to witness this overclocking festival , and this is my second time after I saw an overclocking test at 2007 COMPUTEX Taipei .
#Text=What portion of the computing population most often try to overclock their computers ?
#Text=: Generally , gamers often try overclocking because several games perform best when graphics display and computing are at optimal conditions .
#Text=They needs high-level hardware to fulfill the requirements of those games .
#Text=But some senior engineers also try overclocking tests to examine performance on newly-developed hardware before marketing it .
#Text=Roughly speaking , any user who understands hardware functioning may experiment with overclocking .
#Text=I remember that in a conference , an expert recommended engineers to be cautious for safety reasons , why is that ?
#Text=: If someone wants to try overclocking , all hardware should be waterproof and safety is a paramount issue that experts should be concerned about .
#Text=If they know the risks and can afford the results of overclocking , then the public can rely on those experts when they do overclocking .
#Text=Which software is recommended when overclocking hardware ?
#Text=: 3D Mark , CPU-Z , PCMark05 , SysTool , CPUCool , and CPUIdle are often used for overclocking , but it depends on the individual users to make their own decisions .
#Text=Generally , most experts recommend 3D Mark and PCMark05 .
#Text=What about overclocking for the general public ?
#Text=: Overclocking has some risks as I mentioned before .
#Text=It 's often attempted by general users or the public who have just witnessed someone doing overclocking .
#Text=But , in fact , if someone does proper research over the Internet before doing overclocking , then an relatively safe overclocking test can be tried .
#Text=Just some facts about TAITRA : a Live Test Center was established at COMPUTEX Taipei in 2005 and 2006 , but it was canceled this year .
#Text=Although some hardware companies won some awards there , what have been the effects of the Live Test Center on the hardware industry ?
#Text=: I remember that a foreign magazine set up this pavilion for companies to examine performances in it .
#Text=If they are seeking to raise the profile of this pavilion by winning awards , I do n't think it 's practical .
#Text=Many thanks , I think lots of concepts should be modified according to your advice .
